						               													<description>&amp;#230;&amp;#155;&amp;#135;&amp;#229;&amp;#164;&amp;#169;&amp;#239;&amp;#188;&amp;#143;&amp;#230;&amp;#150;&amp;#172;&amp;#229;&amp;#144;&amp;#136; Legend (Donten no Kiriai Legend) is a Japanese card game for one or two players. It was originally published as &amp;#230;&amp;#155;&amp;#135;&amp;#229;&amp;#164;&amp;#169;&amp;#239;&amp;#188;&amp;#143;&amp;#230;&amp;#150;&amp;#172;&amp;#229;&amp;#144;&amp;#136; (Donten no Kiriai) in 2017. The designer then spun off a simpler game, &amp;#230;&amp;#155;&amp;#135;&amp;#229;&amp;#164;&amp;#169;&amp;#239;&amp;#188;&amp;#143;&amp;#230;&amp;#150;&amp;#172;&amp;#229;&amp;#144;&amp;#136; Tactics (Donten no Kiriai Tactics) to make it easier to learn the game, and republished this edition as &amp;#230;&amp;#155;&amp;#135;&amp;#229;&amp;#164;&amp;#169;&amp;#239;&amp;#188;&amp;#143;&amp;#230;&amp;#150;&amp;#172;&amp;#229;&amp;#144;&amp;#136; Legends for intermediate and experienced players. It is available free as a Print 'n' Play game to download.&amp;#10;&amp;#10;Two Samurais duel, using basic movement cards and two special attacks each round. The duel continues, round after round, until one of the Samurai succumbs to their wounds.&amp;#10;&amp;#10;The players take a basic deck of six cards, and two special cards from a set of five. Players set up the duelling positions, with the Samurai initially being two steps apart, and then each secretly chooses a hand card face-down. When they are ready, the cards are turned up.&amp;#10;&amp;#10;The basic cards involve the Samurai advancing or retreating, and adopting different stances. If the Samurai move close enough together, and onto the same spot, then a strike might happen. But the Samurai switch between being in a Standing stance, and a Ready stance. So an attack can only be made when the Samurai is Ready, otherwise the player falls back to Standing.&amp;#10;&amp;#10;Basic attacks can be made repeatedly, the card goes back to the player's hand when used. But the Special card attacks are used only once a round, and then discarded.&amp;#10;&amp;#10;A round ends when a successful strike is made, and damage is shown on the attacking card. The player struck loses hit points. The decks are re-sorted and the players gain two Special cards again.&amp;#10;&amp;#10;The first player to lose all their health loses the duel.&amp;#10;user summary&amp;#10;&amp;#10;</description>
